<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" box="[151,801,1642,1667]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1642,1667]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including forewing). Male: 
<quantity box="[708,797,1643,1667]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Brownish. Head and thorax marked with dark irregular markings symmetrically placed on crown, anteriorly and medially on pronotum. Gena and lorum light brownish without markings except a pair of small brownish spots bellow eye. Mesonotum with both ends of the suture bent upward and a dark markings posterad of scutellar suture. Forewings smoky brown, with some transverse veins white and without markings.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Anteclypeus distinctly tapered from base to apex, slightly more than twice as long as basal width, apex concave; clypeal suture weakly arcuate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">
Male abdomen. 
<number box="[394,408,1895,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="2.0">2</number>
T apodeme with submedial lobes very short and rounded laterally; 
<number box="[1228,1239,1895,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="1.0">1</number>
S apodeme with submedial lobes straight, greatly elongated, ca. 4.0 times longer than wide, lateral extension bifurcate, branches subequal in length, dorsal branch slender and lateral branch broad; 
<number box="[898,913,1967,1991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="2.0">2</number>
S apodeme with submedial lobes short, slender and strongly curved mesad.
</paragraph>
