</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1812,2017]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">Male genitalia. Pygofer lateral lobe relatively short, ventral margin strongly concave, posterior margin rounded. Subgenital plate with lateral lobe triangular, not reaching dorsal margin of pygofer lobe. Connective Yshaped, branches longer than stem and weakly divergent. Aedeagus with shaft abruptly narrowed and bent dorsad near midlength and strongly curved anterodorsad near apex in lateral view, lateral margins convex near base and parallel-sided near apex in posterior view, constricted near base in ventral view.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
