<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="431" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="431">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[601,774,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrospinus">
<emphasis box="[601,774,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="431">E. macrospinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration, but differs as follows: subgenital plate lateral lobe short, not extended to dorsal margin of pygofer lobe; 
<number box="[823,834,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="431" value="1.0">1</number>
S apodemes with submedial lobes greatly elongated; aedeagus with shaft beyond atrium straight through most of length in lateral view and abruptly curved apically. This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName box="[435,511,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peri">
<emphasis box="[435,511,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="431">E. peri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[580,651,260,285]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="431">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
